title: NASA planetary science budget remains under stress
summary: Despite a small funding increase for 2023, NASA’s planetary science programs still face “significant stress” financially that contributed to the delay of one mission and could push back the start of others.

title: SpaceX ringing in 2023 with Transporter-6 rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX will begin another busy year with the launch of the Transporter-6 rideshare mission from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station (CCSFS). The mission is due to lift off at 9:56 AM EST (14:56 UTC) on Tuesday, Jan. 3, 2023. Falcon 9’s first stage will return to land at Landing Zone-1 at CCSFS approximately eight and a half minutes after launch.

title: Space solar power experiment, 36 Planet imaging satellites on SpaceX rideshare mission
summary: The 114 small satellites set for launch Tuesday on SpaceX’s first mission of the year include 36 spacecraft for Planet’s commercial remote sensing fleet, a space-based solar power experiment, and space tugs to piggyback payloads into different orbits.

title: Military officials forecast 87 launches from Florida’s Space Coast in 2023
summary: The U.S. Space Force is preparing for as many as 87 launches from Florida’s Space Coast in 2023, including dozens more SpaceX missions and the expected debuts of United Launch Alliance’s Vulcan and Relativity’s Terran 1 rockets.
